- Waits for a specified amount of time before throwing
a no such element exception
- Default wait time is 0.
- Doesn't depend on a certain element state, just time.

Syntax

Take to parameters(time to wait(INTEGER), time measurement(seconds,microseconds,etc))

driver.manage().timeouts().implicityWait(TimeOut, TimeUnit.SECONDS);

Pros
- Easy to implement
- Non-intrusive
- They can be applied to all elements in a script

Cons
- Can take up unnecessary time
-

